</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/574bcb90653cbdfe8319a0503947f11687c2ab83" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:31.791ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle {\overline {a}}=\{b\in \mathbb {Z} \mid a\equiv b{\pmod {m}}\}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>A <b>linear congruence</b> is a modular congruence of the form
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle ax\equiv b{\pmod {m}}.}">
