<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Multiplicative_group_of_integers_modulo_m">Multiplicative group of integers modulo <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">m</span></h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Modular_multiplicative_inverse&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Multiplicative group of integers modulo m"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1320445320" /><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Multiplicative_group_of_integers_modulo_n" title="Multiplicative group of integers modulo n">Multiplicative group of integers modulo n</a></div>
<p>Not every element of a complete residue system modulo <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">m</span> has a modular multiplicative inverse, for instance, zero does not have one if <span class="texhtml"><i>m</i> &gt; 1</span>. After removing the elements of a complete residue system that are not relatively prime to <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">m</span>, what is left is called a <b><a href="/wiki/Reduced_residue_system" title="Reduced residue system">reduced residue system</a></b>, all of whose elements have modular multiplicative inverses. The number of elements in a reduced residue system is <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \phi (m)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>&#x03D5;<!-- ϕ --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi (m)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/52ddd8905bfc0ea59762651f0d18b1ec147006c2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:5.235ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \phi (m)}"></span>, where <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \phi }">
