In <a href="/wiki/Big_O_notation" title="Big O notation">big O notation</a>, this algorithm runs in time <span class="texhtml">O(log<sup>2</sup>(<i>m</i>))</span>, assuming <span class="texhtml">&#124;<span class="nowrap" style="padding-left:0.1em; padding-right:0.1em;"><i>a</i></span>&#124; &lt; <i>m</i></span>, and is considered to be very fast and generally more efficient than its alternative, exponentiation.
