<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Using_Euler's_theorem"><span id="Using_Euler.27s_theorem"></span>Using Euler's theorem</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Modular_multiplicative_inverse&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Using Euler&#039;s theorem"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>As an alternative to the extended Euclidean algorithm, Euler's theorem may be used to compute modular inverses.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>11<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>According to <a href="/wiki/Euler%27s_theorem" title="Euler&#39;s theorem">Euler's theorem</a>, if <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">a</span> is <a href="/wiki/Coprime" class="mw-redirect" title="Coprime">coprime</a> to <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">m</span>, that is, <span class="texhtml">gcd(<i>a</i>, <i>m</i>) = 1</span>, then
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle a^{\phi (m)}\equiv 1{\pmod {m}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>&#x03D5;<!-- ϕ --></mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
            <mi>m</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>&#x2261;<!-- ≡ --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mspace width="1em" />
          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mspace width="0.333em" />
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
