      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle (\mathbb {Z} /m\mathbb {Z} )}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8346630a344336b9080498fcdcb1648b2181aa5a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.113ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle (\mathbb {Z} /m\mathbb {Z} )}"></span><sup>×</sup> <a href="/wiki/If_and_only_if" title="If and only if">if and only if</a> <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">a</span> is <a href="/wiki/Coprime" class="mw-redirect" title="Coprime">coprime</a> to <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">m</span>. Therefore, a modular multiplicative inverse can be found directly:
