<p>It is possible to perform the multiplications in a tree structure rather than linearly to exploit <a href="/wiki/Parallel_computing" title="Parallel computing">parallel computing</a>.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Inverses_modulo_prime_powers_(including_powers_of_2)"><span id="Inverses_modulo_prime_powers_.28including_powers_of_2.29"></span>Inverses modulo prime powers (including powers of 2)</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Modular_multiplicative_inverse&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Inverses modulo prime powers (including powers of 2)"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the case where the modulus <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">M</span> is on the form <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle p^{m}}">
